WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.735 --> 00:00:02.738
Very handsome armor
<i>Not a scratch on it.</i>

2
00:00:02.772 --> 00:00:04.440
People have been swinging
at me for years.

3
00:00:04.475 --> 00:00:05.677
but they always
seem to miss.

4
00:00:05.712 --> 00:00:08.614
You've chosen your
opponents wisely then.

5
00:00:08.648 --> 00:00:10.583
Aah aah!

6
00:00:10.618 --> 00:00:12.253
Why didn't you
get up and fight?

7
00:00:12.287 --> 00:00:15.556
I'm a coward.
My father always says so.

8
00:00:15.591 --> 00:00:17.892
- ( Crowd cheering )
- Gods. who is that?

9
00:00:17.927 --> 00:00:20.495
Littlefinger: <i>They call him the Mountain.</i>
<i>the hound's older brother.</i>

10
00:00:20.529 --> 00:00:23.865
- Sansa: <i>And his opponent?</i>
- Littlefinger: <i>Ser Hugh of the Vale.</i>

11
00:00:23.899 --> 00:00:25.667
( Crowd cheering )

12
00:00:25.701 --> 00:00:28.403
- ( Crowd gasps )
- ( Coughs )

13
00:00:28.437 --> 00:00:32.140
"The lineages of the great
houses of the Seven Kingdoms."

14
00:00:32.174 --> 00:00:35.376
- Did jon Arryn tell you
what he wanted with it?- He d.

15
00:00:35.411 --> 00:00:38.779
There was one phrase
he kept repeating:

16
00:00:38.814 --> 00:00:40.514
"The seed is strong."

17
00:00:40.549 --> 00:00:43.419
You might want to visit
a certain armorer in the city.

18
00:00:43.453 --> 00:00:46.222
<i>My observers saw Lord Arryn</i>
<i>visit this armorer.</i>

19
00:00:46.257 --> 00:00:49.494
- Jory: <i>Find anything?</i>
- King Robert's bastard son.

20
00:00:49.529 --> 00:00:51.663
Jon: <i>Sam's no different</i>
<i>from the rest of us.</i>

21
00:00:51.698 --> 00:00:53.799
There was no place for him in
the world. so he's come here.

22
00:00:53.833 --> 00:00:56.234
He's our brother now and we're
going to protect him.

23
00:00:56.269 --> 00:00:59.505
- Aah!
- And now you've woken the dragon--

24
00:00:59.539 --> 00:01:01.407
- ( metal jangles )
- Uh!

25
00:01:01.441 --> 00:01:03.577
I am the wife
of the great Khal

26
00:01:03.612 --> 00:01:05.780
and I carry his son inside me.

27
00:01:05.815 --> 00:01:08.350
The next time
you raise a hand to me

28
00:01:08.384 --> 00:01:11.187
will be the last time
you have hands.

29
00:01:11.222 --> 00:01:12.790
What is it you hope
to accomplish?

30
00:01:12.824 --> 00:01:14.558
The king called on me
to serve him.

31
00:01:14.593 --> 00:01:16.460
You're just a soldier.
aren't you?

32
00:01:16.495 --> 00:01:19.563
- I was also trained to kill my enemies.
- As was I.

33
00:01:19.598 --> 00:01:22.165
This man came into my house

34
00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:25.102
and conspired
to murder my son.

35
00:01:25.137 --> 00:01:27.138
In the name of King Robert.
seize him.

36
00:01:36.781 --> 00:01:38.950
<i>( Theme music playing )</i>

37
00:01:39.047 --> 00:01:43.047
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Game of Thrones 1x05 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Wolf and the Lion</font>
Original Air Date on May 15. 2011

38
00:01:43.072 --> 00:01:47.072
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

39
00:03:33.461 --> 00:03:38.198
( Horse whinnies )

40
00:03:41.232 --> 00:03:44.168
<i>( Men shouting )</i>

41
00:03:50.978 --> 00:03:53.055
Ned: Does Ser Hugh have
any family in the capital?

42
00:03:53.080 --> 00:03:54.280
No.

43
00:03:56.367 --> 00:03:59.235
I stood vigil for him myself
last night.

44
00:03:59.928 --> 00:04:02.262
He had no one else.

45
00:04:03.126 --> 00:04:05.327
He'd never worn
this armor before.

46
00:04:05.361 --> 00:04:07.596
Bad luck for him--

47
00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:09.798
going against
the Mountain.

48
00:04:09.832 --> 00:04:12.199
Who determines
the draw?

49
00:04:12.234 --> 00:04:14.835
All the knights
draw straws. Lord Stark.

50
00:04:14.870 --> 00:04:16.503
Aye.

51
00:04:16.538 --> 00:04:19.740
But who holds
the straws?

52
00:04:19.775 --> 00:04:22.310
You've done
good work. sisters.

53
00:04:27.917 --> 00:04:30.953
Life is strange.
Not so many years ago

54
00:04:30.988 --> 00:04:32.956
we fought as enemies
at the Trident.

55
00:04:32.990 --> 00:04:35.792
I'm glad we never met
on the field. Ser Barristan.

56
00:04:35.826 --> 00:04:37.727
As is my wife.

57
00:04:37.762 --> 00:04:39.763
I don't think the widow's life
would suit her.

58
00:04:39.798 --> 00:04:42.132
( Chuckles )
You're too modest.

59
00:04:42.166 --> 00:04:44.535
I've seen you cut down
a dozen great knights.

60
00:04:44.569 --> 00:04:46.203
My father once told me

61
00:04:46.237 --> 00:04:48.438
you were the best
he'd ever seen.

62
00:04:48.472 --> 00:04:51.308
I never knew the man to be
wrong about matters of combat.

63
00:04:51.342 --> 00:04:53.644
He was a fine man.
your father.

64
00:04:54.946 --> 00:04:57.047
What the Mad King did to him
was a terrible crime.

65
00:04:57.082 --> 00:04:58.649
And that lad--

66
00:04:58.683 --> 00:05:00.718
he was a squire
until a few months ago.

67
00:05:00.753 --> 00:05:03.354
How could he afford
a new suit of armor?

68
00:05:03.388 --> 00:05:05.856
Perhaps Lord Arryn
left him some money?

69
00:05:07.926 --> 00:05:10.027
I hear the King wants
to joust today.

70
00:05:10.061 --> 00:05:11.728
Yes. that will
never happen.

71
00:05:11.763 --> 00:05:14.564
( Chuckles ) Robert tends to do
what he wants.

72
00:05:14.599 --> 00:05:17.234
If the King got what
he wanted all the time.

73
00:05:17.268 --> 00:05:19.870
he'd still be fighting
a damned rebellion.

74
00:05:24.609 --> 00:05:27.344
It's made too small.
Your Grace. It won't go.

75
00:05:27.379 --> 00:05:29.680
Your mother was
a dumb whore

76
00:05:29.715 --> 00:05:32.116
with a fat ass.
Did you know that?

77
00:05:34.786 --> 00:05:38.255
Look at this idiot!
One ball and no brains.

78
00:05:38.290 --> 00:05:41.025
He can't even put a man's
armor on him properly.

79
00:05:41.059 --> 00:05:43.327
You're too fat
for your armor.

80
00:05:43.361 --> 00:05:46.330
Fat?
Fat. is it?

81
00:05:46.365 --> 00:05:49.567
Is that how you speak
to your King?

82
00:05:51.903 --> 00:05:54.639
( Laughing )

83
00:05:56.675 --> 00:05:58.609
That was funny. is it?

84
00:06:00.712 --> 00:06:02.346
No. Your Grace.

85
00:06:02.381 --> 00:06:05.516
No?
You don't like the Hand's joke?

86
00:06:06.485 --> 00:06:08.352
You're torturing
the poor boy.

87
00:06:08.386 --> 00:06:11.188
You heard the Hand.
The King's too fat for his armor.

88
00:06:11.223 --> 00:06:14.325
Go find the breastplate
stretcher-- now!

89
00:06:15.694 --> 00:06:19.397
- ( Laughter )
- "The breastplate stretcher"?

90
00:06:19.431 --> 00:06:21.765
How long before
he figures it out?

91
00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:23.494
Maybe you should
have one invented.

92
00:06:23.519 --> 00:06:24.819
All right. all right.

93
00:06:24.836 --> 00:06:27.604
But you watch me out there--
I still know how to point a Lance.

94
00:06:27.639 --> 00:06:30.742
You have no business jousting.
Leave that for the young men.

95
00:06:30.776 --> 00:06:34.112
Why. because I'm king?
Piss on that. I want to hit somebody!

96
00:06:34.146 --> 00:06:36.514
- And who's going to hit you back?
- Anybody who can.

97
00:06:36.548 --> 00:06:39.617
- And the last man in his saddle--
- Will be you.

98
00:06:39.651 --> 00:06:41.786
There's not a man
in the Seven Kingdoms

99
00:06:41.820 --> 00:06:43.754
would risk hurting you.

100
00:06:43.789 --> 00:06:46.690
Are you telling me those
cowards would let me win?

101
00:06:46.725 --> 00:06:49.293
Aye.

102
00:06:53.665 --> 00:06:56.166
- Drink.
- I'm not thirsty.

103
00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:58.768
Drink.
Your King commands it.

104
00:07:02.539 --> 00:07:04.441
Gods.

105
00:07:04.475 --> 00:07:06.976
too fat for my armor.

106
00:07:07.945 --> 00:07:10.546
Your squire...
A Lannister boy?

107
00:07:10.580 --> 00:07:13.015
Mm. A bloody idiot.

108
00:07:13.049 --> 00:07:15.150
but Cersei insisted.

109
00:07:15.184 --> 00:07:18.620
I have Jon Arryn
to thank for her.

110
00:07:18.654 --> 00:07:21.790
"Cersei Lannister will make
a good match." she told me.

111
00:07:21.825 --> 00:07:24.694
"You'll need her father
on your side."

112
00:07:26.397 --> 00:07:29.967
I thought being King meant I
could do whatever I wanted.

113
00:07:33.472 --> 00:07:35.540
Enough of this.
Let's go watch 'em ride.

114
00:07:35.574 --> 00:07:38.309
At least I can smell
someone else's blood.

115
00:07:38.343 --> 00:07:40.211
- Robert?
- What?

116
00:07:41.113 --> 00:07:44.014
Oh.
( Laughs )

117
00:07:44.049 --> 00:07:47.051
An inspiring sight
for the people. eh?

118
00:07:47.085 --> 00:07:49.987
Come. bow before your King!
Bow. you shits!

119
00:07:50.021 --> 00:07:51.755
( Polite laughter )

120
00:07:53.258 --> 00:07:55.226
( Cheering )

121
00:08:03.569 --> 00:08:07.071
- Where's Arya?
- At her dancing lessons.

122
00:08:09.308 --> 00:08:11.509
The Knight of the Flowers.

123
00:08:18.283 --> 00:08:20.618
Thank you. Ser Loras.

124
00:08:29.061 --> 00:08:30.828
( Neighs )

125
00:08:41.272 --> 00:08:44.141
( Horse fussing )

126
00:08:51.416 --> 00:08:53.751
Don't let Ser Gregor
hurt him.

127
00:08:53.785 --> 00:08:57.188
- Hey.
- <i>I can't watch.</i>

128
00:08:59.624 --> 00:09:02.125
100 gold dragons
on the Mountain.

129
00:09:02.156 --> 00:09:03.206
I'll take that bet.

130
00:09:03.231 --> 00:09:05.096
Now what will I buy
with 100 gold dragons?

131
00:09:05.629 --> 00:09:08.097
A dozen barrels
of Dornish wine?

132
00:09:08.131 --> 00:09:11.166
Or a girl from
the pleasure houses of Lys?

133
00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:12.455
Or you could even
buy a friend.

134
00:09:12.808 --> 00:09:14.731
He's going to die.

135
00:09:14.770 --> 00:09:17.372
Ser Loras rides well.

136
00:09:19.008 --> 00:09:21.943
( Neighing )

137
00:09:25.649 --> 00:09:27.750
( Fanfare )

138
00:09:41.498 --> 00:09:43.432
- ( Gasps )
- ( Laughs )

139
00:09:47.437 --> 00:09:49.304
Such a shame.
Littlefinger.

140
00:09:49.338 --> 00:09:51.639
It would have been so nice
for you to have a friend.

141
00:09:53.108 --> 00:09:54.909
And tell me. Lord Renly.

142
00:09:54.943 --> 00:09:57.445
when will you be having
<i>your</i> friend?

143
00:09:58.680 --> 00:10:00.982
( Neighs )

144
00:10:07.924 --> 00:10:09.759
Loras knew his mare
was in heat.

145
00:10:09.793 --> 00:10:11.527
<i>Quite crafty. really.</i>

146
00:10:11.562 --> 00:10:13.863
Ser Loras would
never do that.

147
00:10:13.898 --> 00:10:15.226
<i>There's no honor in tricks.</i>

148
00:10:15.251 --> 00:10:17.036
No honor and quite
a bit of gold.

149
00:10:19.003 --> 00:10:21.672
- <i>( Helmet clanks )</i>
- Sword!

150
00:10:31.615 --> 00:10:33.850
<i>( Horse neighs )</i>

151
00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:38.722
- ( Gasps )
- ( Neighs )

152
00:10:41.092 --> 00:10:43.026
- ( Gasps )
- ( Grunts )

153
00:10:46.899 --> 00:10:49.000
Leave him be!

154
00:10:58.477 --> 00:11:00.178
( Growls )

155
00:11:10.957 --> 00:11:14.226
Stop this madness
in the name of your King!

156
00:11:19.898 --> 00:11:22.166
Robert:
<i>Let him go!</i>

157
00:11:30.609 --> 00:11:33.078
I owe you my life. Ser.

158
00:11:33.112 --> 00:11:35.380
I'm no Ser.

159
00:11:36.782 --> 00:11:39.984
( Cheering )

160
00:11:58.869 --> 00:12:00.236
Remove his hood.

161
00:12:00.270 --> 00:12:03.206
Marillion: <i>♪ on that Eve.</i>
<i>the captive Imp ♪</i>

162
00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:06.209
♪ downwards
from his horse did limp ♪

163
00:12:06.243 --> 00:12:09.846
<i>♪ no more would he</i>
<i>preen and primp ♪</i>

164
00:12:09.881 --> 00:12:12.217
♪ in garb of red and gold. ♪

165
00:12:12.242 --> 00:12:13.317
Tyrion: This isn't the Kingsroad.

166
00:12:13.318 --> 00:12:15.185
You said we were
riding for Winterfell.

167
00:12:15.220 --> 00:12:17.555
I did...
Often and loudly.

168
00:12:17.589 --> 00:12:19.891
Very wise.

169
00:12:19.926 --> 00:12:21.727
They'll be out
in droves.

170
00:12:21.761 --> 00:12:23.761
looking for me
in the wrong place.

171
00:12:23.796 --> 00:12:26.465
Word's probably gotten
to my father by now.

172
00:12:26.499 --> 00:12:29.301
He'll be offering
a handsome reward.

173
00:12:29.335 --> 00:12:32.705
Everyone knows a Lannister
always pays his debts.

174
00:12:32.739 --> 00:12:35.241
Would you be so good
as to untie me?

175
00:12:35.276 --> 00:12:38.411
- And why would I do that?
- Why not?

176
00:12:38.445 --> 00:12:40.079
Am I going to run?

177
00:12:40.113 --> 00:12:42.014
The hill tribes would
kill me for my boots.

178
00:12:42.049 --> 00:12:43.816
Unless a Shadowcat
ate me first.

179
00:12:43.850 --> 00:12:47.019
Shadowcats and hill tribes are
the least of your concerns.

180
00:12:48.187 --> 00:12:51.189
Ah. the eastern road.

181
00:12:51.223 --> 00:12:53.425
We're going to the Vale.

182
00:12:53.459 --> 00:12:55.460
You're taking me
to your sister's

183
00:12:55.494 --> 00:12:57.395
to answer for my
imagined crimes.

184
00:12:57.430 --> 00:13:00.832
Tell me. Lady Stark. when was
the last time you saw your sister?

185
00:13:00.866 --> 00:13:02.934
Five years ago.

186
00:13:02.969 --> 00:13:05.370
She's changed.

187
00:13:05.405 --> 00:13:07.372
She was always
a bit touched. but now--

188
00:13:07.407 --> 00:13:09.074
you might as well
kill me here.

189
00:13:09.108 --> 00:13:12.044
- I am not a murderer. Lannister.
- Neither am I!

190
00:13:12.078 --> 00:13:14.813
I had nothing to do with the
attempt on your son's life.

191
00:13:14.848 --> 00:13:16.915
- The dagger found--
- What sort of imbecile

192
00:13:16.950 --> 00:13:18.617
arms an assassin
with his own blade?

193
00:13:18.651 --> 00:13:20.852
- Should I gag him?
- Why?

194
00:13:20.886 --> 00:13:22.754
Am I starting
to make sense?

195
00:13:22.788 --> 00:13:25.723
- ( Thuds. grunts )
- Catelyn: <i>Rodrik!</i>

196
00:13:25.757 --> 00:13:27.692
( Screaming )

197
00:13:29.394 --> 00:13:31.395
<i>My Lady. this way.</i>

198
00:13:47.381 --> 00:13:49.182
Untie me.

199
00:13:49.216 --> 00:13:51.584
If I die. what's the point?

200
00:13:56.056 --> 00:13:58.357
( Neighs )

201
00:13:58.392 --> 00:13:59.692
Ah!

202
00:14:05.199 --> 00:14:07.200
( Screams )

203
00:14:40.833 --> 00:14:43.001
( Heavy breathing )

204
00:14:43.035 --> 00:14:44.702
Rodrik?

205
00:14:44.737 --> 00:14:46.404
I'll be fine. My Lady.

206
00:14:46.438 --> 00:14:49.140
<i>There's no need</i>
<i>to bloody yourself.</i>

207
00:14:50.609 --> 00:14:52.376
Your first?

208
00:14:53.712 --> 00:14:55.646
You need a woman.

209
00:14:55.680 --> 00:14:58.616
Nothing like a woman
after a fight.

210
00:15:00.486 --> 00:15:02.554
I'm willing if she is.

211
00:15:02.588 --> 00:15:04.923
( Laughing )

212
00:15:15.035 --> 00:15:16.869
Bran.

213
00:15:16.903 --> 00:15:18.871
Bran: <i>The Iron Islands.</i>

214
00:15:18.905 --> 00:15:20.372
Sigil: A Kraken.

215
00:15:20.407 --> 00:15:23.141
Words: We do not sow.

216
00:15:23.176 --> 00:15:25.310
- Lords?
- The Greyjoys.

217
00:15:25.345 --> 00:15:26.978
Famed for their skills
at archery.

218
00:15:27.012 --> 00:15:28.813
navigation
and lovemaking.

219
00:15:28.847 --> 00:15:30.514
( Laughs )

220
00:15:30.549 --> 00:15:32.816
And failed rebellions.

221
00:15:34.452 --> 00:15:36.320
Sigil: A stag--

222
00:15:36.354 --> 00:15:38.956
a crowned stag
now that Robert's King.

223
00:15:38.990 --> 00:15:42.192
- <i>Good.</i>
- Words: Ours is the fury.

224
00:15:42.227 --> 00:15:44.896
- Lords: The Baratheons.
- Mm-hmm.

225
00:15:44.930 --> 00:15:46.931
<i>The Westerlands.</i>

226
00:15:46.966 --> 00:15:49.034
- Sigil: A lion.
- Mmm.

227
00:15:49.068 --> 00:15:51.441
Words: A Lannister
always pays his debts.

228
00:15:51.466 --> 00:15:52.504
<i>No.</i>

229
00:15:52.613 --> 00:15:54.842
A common saying. but not
their official motto.

230
00:15:55.209 --> 00:15:57.911
- <i>( Arrow thunks )</i>
- Lords: The Lannisters.

231
00:15:57.945 --> 00:16:00.847
- We're still on their words.
- I don't know them.

232
00:16:00.881 --> 00:16:02.715
You do know them.
Think.

233
00:16:02.749 --> 00:16:05.151
"Unbowed. unbent.
unbroken."

234
00:16:05.185 --> 00:16:07.819
- That's House Martell.
- "Righteous in wrath."

235
00:16:07.854 --> 00:16:11.823
- House Hornwood.
- "Family. duty. honor."

236
00:16:11.858 --> 00:16:13.825
<i>Those are Tully words--</i>
<i>your mother's.</i>

237
00:16:13.859 --> 00:16:16.961
- Are we playing a game?
- Family. duty. honor...

238
00:16:16.995 --> 00:16:19.630
- Is that the right order?
- You know it is.

239
00:16:19.664 --> 00:16:21.999
Family comes first?

240
00:16:22.033 --> 00:16:24.635
Your mother had
to leave Winterfell

241
00:16:24.669 --> 00:16:26.303
to protect the family.

242
00:16:26.337 --> 00:16:28.605
How can she <i>protect</i>
the family

243
00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:31.308
if she's not
<i>with</i> her family?

244
00:16:31.342 --> 00:16:34.745
Your mother
sat by your bed

245
00:16:34.780 --> 00:16:37.448
for three weeks
while you slept--

246
00:16:37.482 --> 00:16:39.917
and then she left!

247
00:16:41.754 --> 00:16:42.986
When you were born.
I was the one

248
00:16:43.011 --> 00:16:44.404
who pulled you
from your mother.

249
00:16:45.825 --> 00:16:48.461
<i>I placed you in her arms.</i>

250
00:16:48.495 --> 00:16:52.398
From that moment
until the moment she dies.

251
00:16:52.433 --> 00:16:55.702
she will love you.

252
00:16:55.736 --> 00:16:58.806
<i>Absolutely.</i>

253
00:16:58.840 --> 00:17:02.109
- <i>Fiercely.</i>
- Why did she leave?

254
00:17:02.144 --> 00:17:04.078
( Sighs )
I still can't tell you.

255
00:17:04.112 --> 00:17:06.280
- but she will be home soon.
- Do you know where she is now?

256
00:17:06.315 --> 00:17:08.249
- <i>( Arrow thunks )</i>
- Today?

257
00:17:08.284 --> 00:17:09.461
No. I don't.

258
00:17:09.486 --> 00:17:11.832
Then how can you promise me
she'll be home soon?

259
00:17:14.758 --> 00:17:18.427
Sometimes I worry you're too
smart for your own good.

260
00:17:19.529 --> 00:17:22.198
I'll never shoot
another arrow.

261
00:17:22.232 --> 00:17:24.867
And where is that written?

262
00:17:26.036 --> 00:17:28.070
- You need legs to work a bow.
- Hmm.

263
00:17:28.104 --> 00:17:30.806
If the saddle Lord Tyrion
designed actually works.

264
00:17:30.840 --> 00:17:32.840
you could learn to shoot a bow
from horseback.

265
00:17:32.875 --> 00:17:34.909
Really

266
00:17:36.277 --> 00:17:38.712
Dothraki boys learn
when they're four years old.

267
00:17:38.746 --> 00:17:40.348
Why shouldn't you?

268
00:17:45.354 --> 00:17:47.422
( Grunting )

269
00:17:52.062 --> 00:17:54.897
( Moans )

270
00:17:55.799 --> 00:17:57.967
Shh. keep it down.

271
00:17:58.002 --> 00:18:00.570
You're not supposed to be
inside the castle walls.

272
00:18:00.605 --> 00:18:04.073
I thought you were supposed to be
an important person around here.

273
00:18:04.108 --> 00:18:06.876
Important enough
for the likes of you.

274
00:18:06.910 --> 00:18:09.879
You're not the only nobleman
in my life. you know.

275
00:18:09.914 --> 00:18:11.848
Who. the Imp?

276
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:13.750
I'd call him
half a nobleman.

277
00:18:13.784 --> 00:18:15.618
Jealous?

278
00:18:15.653 --> 00:18:17.587
Why should I be jealous?

279
00:18:17.621 --> 00:18:20.624
Anyone with a few coppers in his
pocket can own you for the night.

280
00:18:20.658 --> 00:18:23.626
What's a dwarf like
down below?

281
00:18:23.661 --> 00:18:25.762
I've always wondered.

282
00:18:25.797 --> 00:18:28.465
- Might surprise you.
- Hmm?

283
00:18:28.500 --> 00:18:31.501
He's good
with his fingers too.

284
00:18:31.536 --> 00:18:33.637
And his tongue.

285
00:18:34.539 --> 00:18:36.339
Generous tipper.

286
00:18:36.374 --> 00:18:39.109
I guess gold is cheap
for a Lannister.

287
00:18:39.143 --> 00:18:41.144
You are jealous.

288
00:18:41.178 --> 00:18:42.846
I'm a Greyjoy.

289
00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:45.115
We've been lords of the
Iron Islands for 300 years.

290
00:18:45.149 --> 00:18:48.252
There's not a family in Westeros
that can look down on us.

291
00:18:48.286 --> 00:18:50.187
not even the Lannisters.

292
00:18:50.222 --> 00:18:52.623
And what about
the Starks?

293
00:18:54.025 --> 00:18:56.660
I've been Lord Stark's ward
since I was eight years old.

294
00:18:56.695 --> 00:18:59.296
A ward--
that's a nice word for it.

295
00:18:59.330 --> 00:19:01.765
Your father rebelled
against King Robert

296
00:19:01.799 --> 00:19:04.267
- and if he does it again--
- My father fought

297
00:19:04.301 --> 00:19:06.436
for the freedom
of his people.

298
00:19:06.470 --> 00:19:09.906
What did your father do?
Fucked a cook and whelped a whore.

299
00:19:09.940 --> 00:19:12.508
You're a very serious boy.

300
00:19:12.543 --> 00:19:16.146
- I'm not a boy.
- Oh yes. you are.

301
00:19:16.180 --> 00:19:20.216
A serious boy
with a serious cock.

302
00:19:20.251 --> 00:19:22.819
I don't want
to pay for it.

303
00:19:22.853 --> 00:19:25.855
Then get yourself
a wife.

304
00:19:28.726 --> 00:19:31.428
- Arya: <i>Come on.</i>
- ( Meows )

305
00:19:32.763 --> 00:19:35.232
- I'm not gonna hurt you.
- ( Meows )

306
00:19:39.937 --> 00:19:41.404
( Meows )

307
00:19:42.773 --> 00:19:45.141
How is your son.
My Lord?

308
00:19:45.175 --> 00:19:48.177
He'll never
walk again.

309
00:19:50.080 --> 00:19:52.015
But his mind is sound?

310
00:19:52.049 --> 00:19:54.217
So they say.

311
00:19:54.251 --> 00:19:56.686
A blessing then.

312
00:19:58.122 --> 00:20:01.692
I suffered an early
mutilation myself.

313
00:20:03.261 --> 00:20:05.863
Some doors
close forever...

314
00:20:05.898 --> 00:20:09.535
Others open
in the most unexpected places.

315
00:20:11.471 --> 00:20:13.239
May I?

316
00:20:17.478 --> 00:20:20.747
If the wrong ears heard
what I'm about to tell you.

317
00:20:20.781 --> 00:20:22.916
off comes my head.

318
00:20:22.950 --> 00:20:25.585
And who would mourn
poor Varys then?

319
00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:29.289
North or South. they sing
no songs for spiders.

320
00:20:29.323 --> 00:20:31.858
But there are things
you must know.

321
00:20:31.892 --> 00:20:34.961
You are the King's Hand
and the King is a fool--

322
00:20:34.995 --> 00:20:37.230
your friend. I know.
but a fool--

323
00:20:37.264 --> 00:20:40.232
and doomed
unless you save him.

324
00:20:40.266 --> 00:20:42.567
I've been in the capital
a month.

325
00:20:43.803 --> 00:20:46.537
Why have you waited so long
to tell me this?

326
00:20:46.572 --> 00:20:48.706
I didn't trust you.

327
00:20:48.740 --> 00:20:51.074
So why do you trust me now?

328
00:20:51.109 --> 00:20:53.310
The Queen is
not the only one

329
00:20:53.344 --> 00:20:55.745
who has been
watching you closely.

330
00:20:55.779 --> 00:20:58.314
There are few men of honor
in the capital.

331
00:20:58.348 --> 00:21:00.015
You are one of them.

332
00:21:00.050 --> 00:21:02.084
I would like to believe
I am another.

333
00:21:02.118 --> 00:21:04.086
strange as that may seem.

334
00:21:04.120 --> 00:21:06.789
What sort of doom
does the King face?

335
00:21:06.823 --> 00:21:09.792
The same sort
as Jon Arryn.

336
00:21:11.028 --> 00:21:13.496
<i>The tears of Lys.</i>
<i>they call it.</i>

337
00:21:13.530 --> 00:21:16.132
<i>A rare and costly thing.</i>

338
00:21:16.167 --> 00:21:17.901
as clear
and tasteless as water.

339
00:21:17.935 --> 00:21:20.070
It leaves no trace.

340
00:21:28.982 --> 00:21:30.850
Who gave it to him?

341
00:21:30.884 --> 00:21:33.787
Some dear friend. no doubt.
But which one?

342
00:21:33.821 --> 00:21:35.489
There were many.

343
00:21:35.523 --> 00:21:38.225
Lord Arryn was a kind
and trusting man.

344
00:21:38.259 --> 00:21:40.627
( Sighs )
There was one boy.

345
00:21:40.661 --> 00:21:43.329
All he was
he owed to Jon Arryn.

346
00:21:43.364 --> 00:21:46.166
The squire. Ser Hugh?

347
00:21:48.336 --> 00:21:50.337
Pity what happened
to him.

348
00:21:50.372 --> 00:21:53.441
just when his life seemed
to be going so nicely.

349
00:21:55.310 --> 00:21:57.978
If Ser Hugh poisoned him--

350
00:21:58.012 --> 00:22:00.813
who paid Ser Hugh?

351
00:22:02.182 --> 00:22:04.016
Someone who could afford it.

352
00:22:04.050 --> 00:22:06.419
Jon was a man of peace.

353
00:22:06.453 --> 00:22:08.420
He was Hand for 17 years--

354
00:22:08.455 --> 00:22:10.589
17 good years.

355
00:22:10.624 --> 00:22:12.424
Why kill him?

356
00:22:12.459 --> 00:22:16.862
He started
asking questions.

357
00:22:22.101 --> 00:22:23.936
( Meows )

358
00:22:45.224 --> 00:22:48.060
Man's voice:
<i>He's found one bastard already.</i>

359
00:22:48.094 --> 00:22:50.228
He has the book.

360
00:22:50.263 --> 00:22:52.264
- The rest will come.
- <i>( Lock clicks )</i>

361
00:22:52.298 --> 00:22:54.867
Man #2: <i>And when he knows</i>
<i>the truth. what will he do?</i>

362
00:22:54.901 --> 00:22:56.802
<i>The gods alone know.</i>

363
00:22:56.836 --> 00:22:59.471
The fools tried
to kill his son.

364
00:22:59.505 --> 00:23:02.641
What's worse--
they botched it.

365
00:23:05.111 --> 00:23:08.080
The wolf and the lion will
be at each other's throats.

366
00:23:08.115 --> 00:23:11.750
- <i>We will be at war soon. my friend.</i>
- <i>What good is war now?</i>

367
00:23:11.785 --> 00:23:13.586
We're not ready.

368
00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:16.222
If one Hand can die.
why not a second?

369
00:23:16.256 --> 00:23:18.991
This Hand
is not the other.

370
00:23:19.026 --> 00:23:20.993
<i>We need time.</i>

371
00:23:21.028 --> 00:23:23.663
Khal Drogo will not make his
move until his son is born.

372
00:23:23.697 --> 00:23:25.832
You know how
these savages are.

373
00:23:25.866 --> 00:23:29.536
<i>"Delay." you say.</i>
<i>"Move fast." I reply.</i>

374
00:23:29.570 --> 00:23:32.872
<i>This is no longer</i>
<i>a game for two players.</i>

375
00:23:32.907 --> 00:23:35.408
<i>It never was.</i>

376
00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:57.663
The first to arrive
and the last to leave.

377
00:23:59.232 --> 00:24:01.534
I admire
your industry.

378
00:24:01.568 --> 00:24:03.702
You do move quietly.

379
00:24:03.737 --> 00:24:06.638
We all have
our qualities.

380
00:24:08.074 --> 00:24:09.908
You look
a bit lonely today.

381
00:24:09.942 --> 00:24:12.210
You should pay a visit to
my brothel this evening.

382
00:24:12.244 --> 00:24:13.707
First boy is on the house.

383
00:24:13.732 --> 00:24:15.879
I think you're mistaking
business with pleasure.

384
00:24:16.081 --> 00:24:18.049
Am I?

385
00:24:19.384 --> 00:24:21.686
All those birds that
whisper in your ear--

386
00:24:21.720 --> 00:24:23.820
such pretty little things.

387
00:24:24.856 --> 00:24:27.323
Trust me.

388
00:24:27.358 --> 00:24:30.159
we accommodate
all inclinations.

389
00:24:30.194 --> 00:24:31.894
Oh. I'm sure.

390
00:24:31.929 --> 00:24:35.097
Lord Redwyne likes his boys
very young. I hear.

391
00:24:35.131 --> 00:24:38.433
I'm a purveyor
of beauty <i>and</i> discretion--

392
00:24:38.468 --> 00:24:40.136
both equally important.

393
00:24:40.170 --> 00:24:43.907
Though I suppose beauty
is a subjective quality. no?

394
00:24:43.941 --> 00:24:45.642
Is it true that

395
00:24:45.677 --> 00:24:48.979
Ser Marlon of Tumblestone
prefers amputees?

396
00:24:49.014 --> 00:24:52.216
All desires are valid
to a man with a full purse.

397
00:24:52.251 --> 00:24:55.820
And I heard the most awful
rumor about a certain lord

398
00:24:55.855 --> 00:24:57.856
with a taste
for fresh cadavers.

399
00:24:57.891 --> 00:25:02.261
Must be enormously difficult
to accommodate that inclination.

400
00:25:02.295 --> 00:25:04.196
The logistics alone--

401
00:25:04.230 --> 00:25:07.599
to find beautiful corpses
before they rot.

402
00:25:07.634 --> 00:25:09.602
Strictly speaking.
such a thing

403
00:25:09.636 --> 00:25:11.904
would not be in accordance
with the King's laws.

404
00:25:11.938 --> 00:25:14.506
Strictly speaking.

405
00:25:17.077 --> 00:25:19.611
Tell me--
does someone somewhere

406
00:25:19.646 --> 00:25:23.181
keep your balls
in a little box?

407
00:25:23.216 --> 00:25:25.650
I've often wondered.

408
00:25:26.986 --> 00:25:28.887
Do you know I have no idea
where they are?

409
00:25:28.921 --> 00:25:32.057
- And we had been so close.
- ( Chuckles )

410
00:25:32.091 --> 00:25:34.559
But enough about me.
How have you been

411
00:25:34.593 --> 00:25:36.561
since we last
saw each other?

412
00:25:36.595 --> 00:25:39.364
Since you last saw me
or since I last saw you?

413
00:25:39.398 --> 00:25:40.937
Now the last time
I saw you.

414
00:25:40.962 --> 00:25:42.587
you were talking
to the Hand of the King.

415
00:25:42.768 --> 00:25:45.803
- Saw me with your own eyes?
- Eyes I own.

416
00:25:45.837 --> 00:25:47.370
Council business.

417
00:25:47.404 --> 00:25:50.473
We all have so much
to discuss with Ned Stark.

418
00:25:50.507 --> 00:25:53.509
Everyone's well aware
of your enduring fondness

419
00:25:53.543 --> 00:25:55.444
for Lord Stark's wife.

420
00:25:55.478 --> 00:25:59.448
If the Lannisters were behind
the attempt on the Stark boy's life

421
00:25:59.482 --> 00:26:01.497
and it was discovered
that you helped

422
00:26:01.522 --> 00:26:03.642
the Starks come
to that conclusion...

423
00:26:05.322 --> 00:26:08.491
To think a simple word
to the Queen--

424
00:26:08.526 --> 00:26:11.028
- one shudders at the thought.
- Ooh.

425
00:26:11.063 --> 00:26:13.698
But you know something?
I do believe that I have seen <i>you</i>

426
00:26:13.732 --> 00:26:15.600
even more recently
than you have seen me.

427
00:26:15.634 --> 00:26:18.537
- Have you?
- Yes.

428
00:26:18.571 --> 00:26:20.372
Earlier today.
I distinctly recall

429
00:26:20.407 --> 00:26:22.808
seeing you talking to Lord Stark
in his chambers.

430
00:26:22.842 --> 00:26:25.044
Was that you
under the bed?

431
00:26:25.078 --> 00:26:26.946
And not long after that

432
00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:29.949
when I saw you
escorting a certain

433
00:26:29.983 --> 00:26:32.651
<i>foreign</i> dignitary...

434
00:26:32.685 --> 00:26:35.287
Council business?

435
00:26:35.322 --> 00:26:38.891
Of course you would have friends
from across the Narrow Sea.

436
00:26:38.925 --> 00:26:41.427
You're from there
yourself. after all.

437
00:26:41.461 --> 00:26:44.797
We're friends.
aren't we. Lord Varys?

438
00:26:44.832 --> 00:26:47.000
I'd like to think we are.

439
00:26:47.034 --> 00:26:49.403
So you can imagine
my burden.

440
00:26:49.437 --> 00:26:53.307
wondering if the King might
question my friend's sympathies.

441
00:26:53.341 --> 00:26:57.378
To stand at a crossroads where
turning left means loyalty to a friend.

442
00:26:57.412 --> 00:26:59.279
turning right
loyalty to the realm--

443
00:26:59.314 --> 00:27:01.448
- Oh. please.
- To find myself in a position

444
00:27:01.482 --> 00:27:03.750
- where a simple word to the King--
- <i>( Door opens )</i>

445
00:27:03.784 --> 00:27:05.819
What are you two
conspiring about?

446
00:27:05.853 --> 00:27:09.423
Well. whatever it is.
you'd best hurry up.

447
00:27:09.458 --> 00:27:10.991
My brother is coming.

448
00:27:11.026 --> 00:27:12.693
To a small council meeting?

449
00:27:12.727 --> 00:27:15.729
Disturbing news
from far away.

450
00:27:16.731 --> 00:27:18.365
Haven't you heard?

451
00:27:20.101 --> 00:27:22.403
<i>( Birds cawing.</i>
<i>waves breaking )</i>

452
00:27:48.232 --> 00:27:50.300
Off with you.
No begging.

453
00:27:50.335 --> 00:27:52.136
I'm not a beggar.
I live here.

454
00:27:52.170 --> 00:27:54.572
D'you want a smack on your ear
to help you with your hearing?

455
00:27:54.606 --> 00:27:56.507
I want to see my father.

456
00:27:56.542 --> 00:27:59.276
I want to fuck the Queen.
for all the good it does me.

457
00:27:59.311 --> 00:28:01.144
You want your father. boy?

458
00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:03.346
He's lying on the floor
of some tavern.

459
00:28:03.381 --> 00:28:05.448
getting pissed on
by his friends.

460
00:28:05.482 --> 00:28:07.183
My father
is Hand of the King!

461
00:28:07.218 --> 00:28:10.520
I'm not a boy.
I'm Arya Stark of Winterfell

462
00:28:10.554 --> 00:28:12.149
and if you lay a hand on me.
my father

463
00:28:12.174 --> 00:28:13.713
will have both
your heads on spikes.

464
00:28:14.091 --> 00:28:16.559
Now are you going to let me by
or do I need to smack you

465
00:28:16.593 --> 00:28:19.061
on the ear to help
with your hearing?

466
00:28:21.198 --> 00:28:24.434
You know I had half my guard
out searching for you?

467
00:28:27.639 --> 00:28:29.406
You promised me
this would stop.

468
00:28:29.441 --> 00:28:31.075
They said they were
going to kill you.

469
00:28:31.110 --> 00:28:33.578
- Who did?
- I didn't see them.

470
00:28:33.613 --> 00:28:35.881
- but I think one was fat.
- Oh. Arya. ( Sighs )

471
00:28:35.916 --> 00:28:38.651
I'm not lying!
They said you found the bastard

472
00:28:38.685 --> 00:28:41.654
and the wolves are fighting
the lions and the savage--

473
00:28:41.688 --> 00:28:43.355
something about the savage.

474
00:28:43.390 --> 00:28:45.757
- Where did you hear this?
- In the dungeons.

475
00:28:45.791 --> 00:28:47.196
near the dragon skulls.

476
00:28:47.221 --> 00:28:48.556
What were you doing
in the dungeons?

477
00:28:50.296 --> 00:28:52.397
Chasing a cat.

478
00:28:52.431 --> 00:28:54.799
<i>( Knocks. door opens )</i>

479
00:28:54.834 --> 00:28:56.167
Pardon. My Lord.

480
00:28:56.202 --> 00:28:58.336
<i>There's a night's watchman</i>
<i>here begging a word.</i>

481
00:28:58.370 --> 00:28:59.670
<i>He says it's urgent.</i>

482
00:29:06.611 --> 00:29:10.547
- Your name. friend?
- Yoren. if it please.

483
00:29:10.581 --> 00:29:12.424
This must be your son.
He has the look.

484
00:29:12.449 --> 00:29:13.549
I'm a girl!

485
00:29:13.567 --> 00:29:15.034
Did Benjen send you?

486
00:29:15.051 --> 00:29:16.885
No one sent me.
My Lord.

487
00:29:16.919 --> 00:29:19.154
I'm here to find
men for the Wall.

488
00:29:19.188 --> 00:29:20.950
see if there's any scum
in the dungeons

489
00:29:20.975 --> 00:29:22.175
that might be fit for service.

490
00:29:22.259 --> 00:29:24.493
Oh. we'll find
recruits for you.

491
00:29:24.527 --> 00:29:25.994
Thank you. My Lord.

492
00:29:26.029 --> 00:29:28.497
But that's not why
I disturb you now.

493
00:29:29.733 --> 00:29:32.435
Your brother Benjen.
his blood runs black--

494
00:29:32.469 --> 00:29:34.537
makes him as much
my brother as yours.

495
00:29:34.571 --> 00:29:37.507
It's for his sake
I rode here so hard

496
00:29:37.541 --> 00:29:40.143
<i>I damn near</i>
<i>killed my horse.</i>

497
00:29:40.177 --> 00:29:41.878
There are others
riding too.

498
00:29:41.912 --> 00:29:43.981
The whole city
will know by tomorrow.

499
00:29:44.015 --> 00:29:45.716
Know what?

500
00:29:47.219 --> 00:29:49.854
Best said
in private. My Lord.

501
00:29:55.095 --> 00:29:58.365
Go on.
We'll talk more later.

502
00:29:58.399 --> 00:30:01.000
Jory. take her
safely to her room.

503
00:30:01.035 --> 00:30:04.170
Come along. My Lady.
You heard your father.

504
00:30:09.676 --> 00:30:11.610
How many guards
does my father have?

505
00:30:11.645 --> 00:30:13.846
Here in
King's Landing? 50.

506
00:30:15.082 --> 00:30:17.249
You wouldn't let anyone
kill him. would you?

507
00:30:17.284 --> 00:30:20.519
No fear on that count.
little lady.

508
00:30:24.891 --> 00:30:28.160
- Well?
- It's about your wife. My Lord.

509
00:30:29.763 --> 00:30:31.597
She's taken the Imp.

510
00:30:42.409 --> 00:30:44.243
( Neighs )

511
00:30:48.648 --> 00:30:50.682
You're far from home.
Lady Stark.

512
00:30:50.716 --> 00:30:52.450
To whom do I speak?

513
00:30:52.485 --> 00:30:54.486
Ser Vardis Egan.
knight of the Vale.

514
00:30:54.520 --> 00:30:56.488
Is Lady Arryn
expecting your visit?

515
00:30:56.522 --> 00:30:58.790
There was no time
to send word.

516
00:30:58.824 --> 00:31:01.025
May I ask. My Lady.

517
00:31:01.060 --> 00:31:03.761
why <i>he</i> is with you?

518
00:31:03.796 --> 00:31:05.830
That's why
there was no time.

519
00:31:05.864 --> 00:31:08.766
- He is my prisoner.
- He doesn't look like a prisoner.

520
00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:12.103
My <i>sister</i> will decide
what he looks like.

521
00:31:12.137 --> 00:31:14.272
Yes. My Lady.

522
00:31:14.306 --> 00:31:16.508
She will at that.

523
00:31:22.381 --> 00:31:25.983
The Eyrie.
They say it's impregnable.

524
00:31:27.285 --> 00:31:29.319
Give me 10 good men
and some climbing spikes--

525
00:31:29.354 --> 00:31:31.221
I'll impregnate the bitch.

526
00:31:32.690 --> 00:31:34.824
Tyrion: I like you.

527
00:31:44.367 --> 00:31:46.601
Lord Stark. your presence
has been requested

528
00:31:46.636 --> 00:31:49.003
in the small council chamber.
A meeting has been called.

529
00:31:49.038 --> 00:31:51.205
I need to see
the King first-- alone.

530
00:31:51.239 --> 00:31:53.674
The King is at the small council
meeting. My Lord.

531
00:31:53.708 --> 00:31:55.442
He has summoned you.

532
00:31:55.476 --> 00:31:58.646
- Is it about my wife?
- No. My Lord.

533
00:31:58.680 --> 00:32:01.616
I believe it concerns
Daenerys Targaryen.

534
00:32:01.650 --> 00:32:04.018
The whore is pregnant.

535
00:32:04.053 --> 00:32:06.988
- You're speaking of murdering a child.
- I warned you

536
00:32:07.023 --> 00:32:09.491
this would happen.
Back in the North. I warned you.

537
00:32:09.526 --> 00:32:11.127
but you didn't care
to hear.

538
00:32:11.161 --> 00:32:13.764
Well. hear it now.

539
00:32:13.798 --> 00:32:17.068
I want 'em dead.
mother and child both.

540
00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:19.237
<i>And that fool Viserys</i>
<i>as well.</i>

541
00:32:19.271 --> 00:32:21.305
Is that plain enough
for you?

542
00:32:21.339 --> 00:32:22.940
<i>I want them both dead.</i>

543
00:32:22.974 --> 00:32:25.509
You will dishonor yourself
forever if you do this.

544
00:32:25.544 --> 00:32:26.544
Honor?!

545
00:32:26.578 --> 00:32:29.246
I've got Seven Kingdoms
to rule!

546
00:32:29.281 --> 00:32:32.049
One King.
Seven Kingdoms.

547
00:32:32.083 --> 00:32:34.518
Do you think honor
keeps them in line?

548
00:32:34.552 --> 00:32:36.987
Do you think it's honor
that's keeping the peace?

549
00:32:37.022 --> 00:32:39.623
It's fear--
fear and blood.

550
00:32:39.657 --> 00:32:41.357
Then we're no better
than the Mad King.

551
00:32:41.392 --> 00:32:43.393
Careful. Ned.
Careful now.

552
00:32:43.427 --> 00:32:45.395
You want
to assassinate a girl

553
00:32:45.429 --> 00:32:47.463
because the Spider
heard a rumor?

554
00:32:47.498 --> 00:32:50.400
No rumor. My Lord.
The princess is with child.

555
00:32:50.434 --> 00:32:52.201
Based on whose
information?

556
00:32:52.235 --> 00:32:53.568
Ser Jorah Mormont.

557
00:32:53.593 --> 00:32:55.881
He is serving as advisor
to the Targaryens.

558
00:32:56.206 --> 00:32:58.340
Mormont?
You bring us the whispers

559
00:32:58.374 --> 00:33:02.077
of a traitor half a world away
and call it fact?

560
00:33:02.112 --> 00:33:05.147
Jorah Mormont's
a slaver. not a traitor.

561
00:33:05.182 --> 00:33:07.584
Small difference. I know.
to an honorable man.

562
00:33:07.618 --> 00:33:10.287
He broke the law. betrayed
his family. fled our land.

563
00:33:10.321 --> 00:33:13.191
We commit murder
on the word of this man?

564
00:33:13.225 --> 00:33:15.193
Robert: <i>And if he's right?</i>

565
00:33:15.227 --> 00:33:17.262
If she has a son?

566
00:33:17.296 --> 00:33:20.431
A Targaryen at the head
of a Dothraki army...

567
00:33:20.466 --> 00:33:24.135
- <i>What then?</i>
- The Narrow Sea still lies between us.

568
00:33:24.170 --> 00:33:26.304
I'll fear the Dothraki

569
00:33:26.338 --> 00:33:28.773
the day they teach
their horses to run on water.

570
00:33:28.807 --> 00:33:30.908
Do nothing?

571
00:33:30.943 --> 00:33:33.111
That's your wise advice?

572
00:33:33.145 --> 00:33:36.247
Do nothing till our enemies
are on our shores?

573
00:33:36.281 --> 00:33:39.116
You're my council.
Counsel!

574
00:33:39.151 --> 00:33:42.986
Speak sense to this
honorable fool.

575
00:33:43.021 --> 00:33:47.023
I understand your misgivings.
My Lord.

576
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:49.726
Truly. I do.
It is a terrible thing

577
00:33:49.760 --> 00:33:51.827
we must consider.
a vile thing.

578
00:33:51.862 --> 00:33:55.096
Yet we who presume
to rule must sometimes

579
00:33:55.131 --> 00:33:58.666
do vile things for
the good of the realm.

580
00:33:58.701 --> 00:34:01.903
Should the gods
grant Daenerys a son.

581
00:34:01.937 --> 00:34:03.671
the realm will bleed.

582
00:34:03.706 --> 00:34:06.007
I bear this girl no ill will.

583
00:34:06.041 --> 00:34:08.109
<i>but should</i>
<i>the Dothraki invade.</i>

584
00:34:08.143 --> 00:34:10.011
how many innocents will die?

585
00:34:10.045 --> 00:34:12.080
How many towns
will burn?

586
00:34:12.114 --> 00:34:15.316
Is it not wiser.
kinder even.

587
00:34:15.350 --> 00:34:17.752
that she should die now

588
00:34:17.786 --> 00:34:21.155
so that tens of thousands
might live?

589
00:34:21.189 --> 00:34:23.691
We should have had them
both killed years ago.

590
00:34:23.725 --> 00:34:26.159
When you find yourself
in bed with an ugly woman.

591
00:34:26.194 --> 00:34:29.529
<i>best close your eyes.</i>
<i>get it over with.</i>

592
00:34:29.564 --> 00:34:32.966
Cut her throat.
Be done with it.

593
00:34:38.872 --> 00:34:41.741
I followed you
into war--

594
00:34:41.775 --> 00:34:43.776
twice.

595
00:34:43.811 --> 00:34:46.046
without doubts.

596
00:34:46.081 --> 00:34:48.015
without second thoughts.

597
00:34:48.049 --> 00:34:51.653
But I will not
follow you now.

598
00:34:51.687 --> 00:34:54.055
The Robert I grew up with

599
00:34:54.090 --> 00:34:57.659
didn't tremble at the shadow
of an unborn child.

600
00:34:59.629 --> 00:35:01.530
She dies.

601
00:35:02.699 --> 00:35:04.800
I will have no part in it.

602
00:35:04.834 --> 00:35:07.102
You're the King's Hand.
Lord Stark.

603
00:35:07.136 --> 00:35:10.805
You'll do as I command
or I'll find me a hand who will.

604
00:35:18.980 --> 00:35:20.814
And good luck to him.

605
00:35:21.883 --> 00:35:23.417
I thought you were
a better man.

606
00:35:23.451 --> 00:35:25.720
Out.
Out. damn you.

607
00:35:25.754 --> 00:35:28.390
I'm done with you.

608
00:35:28.424 --> 00:35:31.393
Go. run back
to Winterfell!

609
00:35:31.428 --> 00:35:34.231
I'll have your head
on a spike!

610
00:35:35.566 --> 00:35:38.502
Robert: <i>I'll put it there</i>
<i>myself. you fool!</i>

611
00:35:38.536 --> 00:35:42.040
<i>You think you're too good for this?</i>
<i>Too proud and honorable?</i>

612
00:35:42.074 --> 00:35:43.841
<i>This is a war!</i>

613
00:35:46.011 --> 00:35:47.846
I'll go ahead
with my daughters.

614
00:35:47.880 --> 00:35:49.448
Get them ready.
Do it yourself.

615
00:35:49.482 --> 00:35:51.918
- Don't ask anyone for help.
- Right away. My Lord.

616
00:35:51.952 --> 00:35:54.087
Lord Baelish
is here for you.

617
00:35:56.224 --> 00:35:58.525
His Grace went on about you
at some length

618
00:35:58.559 --> 00:36:00.794
after you took your leave.

619
00:36:00.828 --> 00:36:02.763
The word "treason"
was mentioned.

620
00:36:04.032 --> 00:36:05.499
What can I do for you?

621
00:36:05.534 --> 00:36:07.300
When do you return
to Winterfell?

622
00:36:07.335 --> 00:36:08.643
Why? What do you care?

623
00:36:08.668 --> 00:36:10.353
If you're still here
come nightfall.

624
00:36:10.538 --> 00:36:12.273
I'll take you to see
the last person Jon Arryn

625
00:36:12.298 --> 00:36:13.798
spoke with before falling ill.

626
00:36:13.907 --> 00:36:16.976
If that sort of thing
still interests you.

627
00:36:17.878 --> 00:36:19.579
I don't have the time.

628
00:36:19.613 --> 00:36:22.248
It won't take more than an hour.
But as you please.

629
00:36:28.188 --> 00:36:29.351
Round up all the men we have

630
00:36:29.376 --> 00:36:30.929
and station them outside
the girls' chambers.

631
00:36:31.457 --> 00:36:35.026
- Who are your best two swords?
- Heward and Wyl.

632
00:36:35.060 --> 00:36:37.762
Find them and meet me
at the stables.

633
00:36:43.135 --> 00:36:45.670
You bring him here
without permission?

634
00:36:45.705 --> 00:36:48.741
<i>You pollute my home</i>
<i>with his presence?</i>

635
00:36:48.775 --> 00:36:51.577
( Suckling )

636
00:36:51.612 --> 00:36:53.546
Your aunt has done
a bad thing. Robin.

637
00:36:53.581 --> 00:36:55.382
a very bad thing.

638
00:36:55.416 --> 00:36:57.885
You remember her.
don't you?

639
00:36:59.188 --> 00:37:01.089
<i>Isn't he beautiful?</i>

640
00:37:01.123 --> 00:37:03.892
And strong too.
Jon knew it.

641
00:37:03.926 --> 00:37:06.961
His last words were
"the seed is strong."

642
00:37:06.995 --> 00:37:08.496
He wanted everyone to know

643
00:37:08.530 --> 00:37:11.799
<i>what a good. strong boy</i>
<i>his son would grow up to be.</i>

644
00:37:11.834 --> 00:37:15.737
Look at him.
the Lord of all the Vale.

645
00:37:15.771 --> 00:37:17.505
Lysa.

646
00:37:17.540 --> 00:37:20.609
you wrote me about
the Lannisters.

647
00:37:20.643 --> 00:37:23.478
- warning me--
- To stay away from them!

648
00:37:23.512 --> 00:37:26.482
Not to bring one here!

649
00:37:26.516 --> 00:37:28.617
Mommy?

650
00:37:28.651 --> 00:37:31.319
- Is that the bad man?
- <i>It is.</i>

651
00:37:31.354 --> 00:37:33.355
( Creepy laugh )

652
00:37:33.389 --> 00:37:36.158
He's little.

653
00:37:36.192 --> 00:37:38.694
Lysa: <i>He's Tyrion the Imp</i>
<i>of House Lannister.</i>

654
00:37:39.696 --> 00:37:41.063
He killed your father.

655
00:37:41.097 --> 00:37:42.798
He murdered
the Hand of the King!

656
00:37:42.833 --> 00:37:45.167
Oh. did I kill him too?

657
00:37:45.201 --> 00:37:47.036
I've been a <i>very</i> busy man.

658
00:37:47.070 --> 00:37:49.738
You will
watch your tongue!

659
00:37:49.772 --> 00:37:52.508
These men are knights
of the Vale.

660
00:37:52.542 --> 00:37:55.377
Every one of them
loved Jon Arryn.

661
00:37:55.412 --> 00:37:57.079
Every one of them would
die for me.

662
00:37:57.113 --> 00:37:58.518
If any harm comes to me.

663
00:37:58.543 --> 00:38:00.691
my brother Jaime will see
that they do.

664
00:38:00.816 --> 00:38:01.890
You can't hurt us.

665
00:38:01.915 --> 00:38:03.549
No one can hurt us here.
Tell him. mommy!

666
00:38:03.820 --> 00:38:07.656
- Tell him!
- Shh shh shh. my sweet boy.

667
00:38:07.691 --> 00:38:10.192
He's just trying
to frighten us.

668
00:38:10.226 --> 00:38:12.060
Lannisters are all liars.

669
00:38:12.095 --> 00:38:15.064
<i>No one will</i>
<i>hurt my baby.</i>

670
00:38:15.098 --> 00:38:17.600
<i>Mommy...</i>

671
00:38:17.634 --> 00:38:20.503
I want to see
the bad man fly.

672
00:38:21.772 --> 00:38:23.573
Perhaps you will.
my little love.

673
00:38:23.608 --> 00:38:25.742
This man is <i>my</i> prisoner.

674
00:38:25.777 --> 00:38:28.779
I will <i>not</i> have him
harmed.

675
00:38:30.816 --> 00:38:32.350
Ser Vardis.

676
00:38:32.384 --> 00:38:35.220
<i>my sister's guest</i>
<i>is weary.</i>

677
00:38:35.254 --> 00:38:38.089
<i>Take him down below</i>
<i>so he can rest.</i>

678
00:38:38.124 --> 00:38:41.325
Introduce him to Mord.

679
00:38:43.495 --> 00:38:44.928
You go sleep.
dwarf man.

680
00:38:44.963 --> 00:38:48.065
( Laughing ) Sleep good.
little dwarf man!

681
00:38:50.902 --> 00:38:53.371
( Slams. lock clanks )

682
00:39:01.580 --> 00:39:04.249
( Wind gusting )

683
00:39:23.401 --> 00:39:25.902
Lord Stark's lucky
he still has a head.

684
00:39:25.937 --> 00:39:28.839
Robert will rant for a few days.
but he won't do anything.

685
00:39:28.873 --> 00:39:30.407
He adores the man.

686
00:39:30.441 --> 00:39:32.209
( Surprised )
You're jealous.

687
00:39:32.243 --> 00:39:34.477
Are you sure
this won't hurt?

688
00:39:34.511 --> 00:39:37.780
- Only if I slip.
- <i>( Scraping )</i>

689
00:39:39.883 --> 00:39:42.684
- And you'd prefer me like this?
- Mm-hmm.

690
00:39:42.719 --> 00:39:45.520
If you want hairless. maybe
you should find a little boy.

691
00:39:45.554 --> 00:39:47.322
I want you.

692
00:39:48.991 --> 00:39:52.192
My brother thinks that anyone
who hasn't been to war isn't a man.

693
00:39:52.227 --> 00:39:54.962
He treats me as if
I'm a spoiled child.

694
00:39:55.963 --> 00:39:58.064
Oh. and you're not?

695
00:39:58.098 --> 00:40:01.434
Loras Tyrell.
the Knight of the Flowers?

696
00:40:01.468 --> 00:40:03.636
How many wars
have you fought in?

697
00:40:03.670 --> 00:40:07.140
Oh. and how much did your father
spend on that armor of yours?

698
00:40:07.174 --> 00:40:09.743
Hold still.

699
00:40:09.777 --> 00:40:12.979
All I ever hear from Robert and
Stannis is how I'm not tough enough.

700
00:40:13.013 --> 00:40:15.081
how I squirm
at the sight of blood--

701
00:40:15.116 --> 00:40:17.651
you did vomit when that boy's eye
was knocked out in the melee.

702
00:40:17.685 --> 00:40:19.615
His eye was dangling
out of the damn socket!

703
00:40:19.640 --> 00:40:21.688
He shouldn't have entered the melee
if he didn't know how to fight.

704
00:40:21.757 --> 00:40:22.957
Easy for you to say.

705
00:40:23.624 --> 00:40:25.559
Not everyone is such
a gifted swordsman.

706
00:40:25.593 --> 00:40:28.094
( Groans ) It's not a gift.
No one gave it to me.

707
00:40:28.129 --> 00:40:30.263
I'm good because
I work at it--

708
00:40:30.297 --> 00:40:33.032
every day of my life
since I could hold a stick.

709
00:40:33.067 --> 00:40:35.401
I could work at fighting
all day. every day.

710
00:40:35.436 --> 00:40:37.337
and still never
be as good as you.

711
00:40:37.371 --> 00:40:39.939
Yes well. I guess
we'll never know.

712
00:40:40.774 --> 00:40:44.143
( Sighs )

713
00:40:49.449 --> 00:40:51.885
- Everywhere?
- Everywhere.

714
00:40:51.919 --> 00:40:54.554
So how did it end up?

715
00:40:54.588 --> 00:40:56.188
The Targaryen
girl will die?

716
00:40:56.223 --> 00:40:59.358
It needs to be done.
unpleasant as it is.

717
00:40:59.392 --> 00:41:01.593
Robert's rather
tasteless about it.

718
00:41:01.628 --> 00:41:03.462
Every time he talks
about killing her.

719
00:41:03.497 --> 00:41:05.665
I swear the table
rises six inches.

720
00:41:05.699 --> 00:41:08.434
It's a shame he can't muster the
same enthusiasm for his wife.

721
00:41:08.468 --> 00:41:11.170
He does have a deep. abiding
lust for her money.

722
00:41:11.205 --> 00:41:13.339
You have to give it
to the Lannisters--

723
00:41:13.373 --> 00:41:15.274
they may be the most
pompous. ponderous cunts

724
00:41:15.308 --> 00:41:16.976
the gods ever suffered
to walk the world.

725
00:41:17.010 --> 00:41:19.678
but they do have outrageous
amounts of money.

726
00:41:20.914 --> 00:41:23.082
I have an outrageous
amount of money.

727
00:41:23.116 --> 00:41:25.083
Not as much
as the Lannisters.

728
00:41:25.117 --> 00:41:27.385
( Laughing )
But a lot more than you.

729
00:41:28.687 --> 00:41:31.388
Robert's threatening
to take me hunting with him.

730
00:41:31.423 --> 00:41:33.757
Last time we were out there
for two weeks.

731
00:41:33.791 --> 00:41:36.359
Tramping through the trees
in the rain. day after day.

732
00:41:36.393 --> 00:41:39.862
all so he can stick his spear
into something's flesh.

733
00:41:39.897 --> 00:41:42.866
Oh. But Robert
loves his killing.

734
00:41:42.900 --> 00:41:45.302
- And he's the King.
- Hmm.

735
00:41:45.336 --> 00:41:48.639
- How did that ever happen?
- Because he loves his killing.

736
00:41:48.673 --> 00:41:50.975
And he used to be
good at it.

737
00:41:51.009 --> 00:41:53.978
Do you know
who should be king?

738
00:41:54.947 --> 00:41:56.848
- Be serious.
- I am.

739
00:41:56.883 --> 00:41:59.184
My father could be
your bank.

740
00:41:59.218 --> 00:42:02.086
I've never fought in a war before.
but I'd fight for you.

741
00:42:02.121 --> 00:42:04.021
I'm fourth in line.

742
00:42:04.056 --> 00:42:06.857
And where was Robert in the line
of royal succession?

743
00:42:06.892 --> 00:42:08.357
Joffrey is a monster.

744
00:42:08.382 --> 00:42:10.093
- Tommen is eight.
- Stannis?

745
00:42:10.155 --> 00:42:12.023
Stannis has the
personality of a lobster.

746
00:42:12.263 --> 00:42:14.230
He's still
my older brother.

747
00:42:14.265 --> 00:42:16.566
- ( Gasps ) What are you doing?!
- Look at it.

748
00:42:16.600 --> 00:42:17.714
You cut me.

749
00:42:17.739 --> 00:42:19.143
It's just blood.
We've all got it in us.

750
00:42:19.269 --> 00:42:21.537
Sometimes a little spills.

751
00:42:21.571 --> 00:42:24.974
If you become King. you're
going to see a lot of this.

752
00:42:25.008 --> 00:42:26.809
You need to get used to it.

753
00:42:26.843 --> 00:42:28.977
Go on. Look.

754
00:42:31.348 --> 00:42:33.582
People love you.

755
00:42:34.884 --> 00:42:36.919
They love to serve you
because you're kind to them.

756
00:42:36.954 --> 00:42:39.121
They want to be near you.

757
00:42:41.525 --> 00:42:44.794
You're willing to do
what needs to be done.

758
00:42:44.828 --> 00:42:47.563
but you don't gloat over it.

759
00:42:47.598 --> 00:42:49.832
You don't love killing.

760
00:42:52.369 --> 00:42:54.670
Where is it written
that power

761
00:42:54.704 --> 00:42:57.472
is the sole province
of the worst?

762
00:42:57.506 --> 00:42:59.574
That thrones are only made

763
00:42:59.608 --> 00:43:01.909
for the hated
and the feared?

764
00:43:05.414 --> 00:43:08.083
You would be
a wonderful King.

765
00:43:25.303 --> 00:43:28.539
I'm sorry your marriage
to Ned Stark didn't work out.

766
00:43:28.573 --> 00:43:30.474
<i>You seemed</i>
<i>so good together.</i>

767
00:43:30.509 --> 00:43:33.544
I'm glad I could do something
to make you happy.

768
00:43:37.315 --> 00:43:40.150
Without a Hand.
everything will fall to pieces.

769
00:43:40.185 --> 00:43:42.152
I suppose this is where
you tell me

770
00:43:42.187 --> 00:43:45.022
to give the job
to your brother Jaime.

771
00:43:45.057 --> 00:43:46.691
No.

772
00:43:46.725 --> 00:43:48.826
He's not serious enough.

773
00:43:48.860 --> 00:43:50.795
I'll say this for Ned Stark:

774
00:43:50.829 --> 00:43:52.930
He's serious enough.

775
00:43:54.166 --> 00:43:56.967
Was it really worth it?
Losing him this way?

776
00:43:57.002 --> 00:43:59.103
I don't know.

777
00:44:01.740 --> 00:44:04.309
But I do know this:

778
00:44:04.343 --> 00:44:09.413
If the Targaryen girl convinces
her horselord husband to invade

779
00:44:09.448 --> 00:44:13.651
and the Dothraki horde
crosses the Narrow Sea...

780
00:44:15.387 --> 00:44:17.221
We won't be able
to stop them.

781
00:44:17.255 --> 00:44:19.757
<i>The Dothraki don't sail.</i>
<i>Every child knows that.</i>

782
00:44:19.791 --> 00:44:22.693
They don't have discipline.
They don't have armor.

783
00:44:22.727 --> 00:44:24.695
They don't have
siege weapons.

784
00:44:24.729 --> 00:44:26.563
It's a neat
little trick you do:

785
00:44:26.598 --> 00:44:29.867
You move your lips and
your father's voice comes out.

786
00:44:29.901 --> 00:44:33.036
( Huffs )
Is my father wrong?

787
00:44:36.341 --> 00:44:39.243
Let's say
Viserys Targaryen lands

788
00:44:39.277 --> 00:44:42.747
with 40.000 Dothraki
screamers at his back.

789
00:44:42.781 --> 00:44:45.282
<i>We hole up</i>
<i>in our castles--</i>

790
00:44:45.317 --> 00:44:48.052
<i>a wise move--</i>
<i>only a fool</i>

791
00:44:48.087 --> 00:44:50.988
<i>would meet the Dothraki</i>
<i>in an open field.</i>

792
00:44:51.022 --> 00:44:53.858
They leave us
in our castles.

793
00:44:53.892 --> 00:44:57.395
They go from town to town.
looting and burning.

794
00:44:57.429 --> 00:45:01.098
<i>killing every man who can't</i>
<i>hide behind a stone wall.</i>

795
00:45:01.132 --> 00:45:04.168
<i>stealing all our crops</i>
<i>and livestock.</i>

796
00:45:04.202 --> 00:45:06.670
enslaving all our women
and children.

797
00:45:06.704 --> 00:45:09.706
How long do the people of the
Seven Kingdoms stand behind

798
00:45:09.741 --> 00:45:13.143
their absentee King.
their cowardly King

799
00:45:13.177 --> 00:45:15.611
hiding behind high walls?

800
00:45:15.646 --> 00:45:18.481
When do the people decide
that Viserys Targaryen

801
00:45:18.515 --> 00:45:21.150
is the rightful monarch
after all?

802
00:45:22.487 --> 00:45:24.621
We still outnumber them.

803
00:45:26.124 --> 00:45:29.627
Which is the bigger number:
Five or one?

804
00:45:30.529 --> 00:45:32.097
Five.

805
00:45:32.999 --> 00:45:34.767
Five...

806
00:45:36.203 --> 00:45:38.171
One.

807
00:45:38.205 --> 00:45:41.174
One army--
a real army

808
00:45:41.208 --> 00:45:44.477
united behind one leader
with one purpose.

809
00:45:46.313 --> 00:45:50.783
Our purpose died
with the Mad King.

810
00:45:50.817 --> 00:45:53.018
Now we've got
as many armies

811
00:45:53.053 --> 00:45:56.622
as there are men
with gold in their purse.

812
00:45:56.656 --> 00:45:59.124
And everybody wants
something different.

813
00:45:59.159 --> 00:46:01.393
Your father wants
to own the world.

814
00:46:01.428 --> 00:46:04.897
Ned Stark wants to run away
and bury his head in the snow.

815
00:46:04.932 --> 00:46:06.532
What do you want?

816
00:46:16.578 --> 00:46:20.314
We haven't had a real fight
in nine years.

817
00:46:20.348 --> 00:46:22.817
Back-stabbing doesn't
prepare you for a fight.

818
00:46:22.851 --> 00:46:25.052
And that's all
the realm is now:

819
00:46:25.087 --> 00:46:27.222
Back-stabbing
and scheming

820
00:46:27.256 --> 00:46:30.959
and arse-licking
and money-grubbing.

821
00:46:30.993 --> 00:46:34.129
Sometimes I don't know
what holds it together.

822
00:46:34.163 --> 00:46:36.531
Our marriage.

823
00:46:36.565 --> 00:46:38.399
( Laughing )

824
00:46:46.542 --> 00:46:49.077
Ah. so here we sit

825
00:46:49.111 --> 00:46:51.379
17 years later.

826
00:46:51.413 --> 00:46:54.048
<i>holding it all together.</i>

827
00:46:55.217 --> 00:46:57.519
Don't you get tired?

828
00:46:57.553 --> 00:46:59.654
Every day.

829
00:47:00.857 --> 00:47:04.327
How long can hate
hold a thing together?

830
00:47:04.361 --> 00:47:08.331
Well. 17 years
is quite a long time.

831
00:47:08.365 --> 00:47:10.499
Yes. it is.

832
00:47:11.635 --> 00:47:13.502
Yes. it is.

833
00:47:18.608 --> 00:47:20.709
What was she like?

834
00:47:23.045 --> 00:47:25.513
You've never asked
about her. not once.

835
00:47:25.548 --> 00:47:27.916
Why not?

836
00:47:27.950 --> 00:47:31.286
At first. just saying
her name even in private

837
00:47:31.321 --> 00:47:35.057
felt like I was breathing
life back into her.

838
00:47:35.091 --> 00:47:37.292
I thought if I didn't
talk about her.

839
00:47:37.326 --> 00:47:39.761
she'd just
fade away for you.

840
00:47:39.796 --> 00:47:42.498
When I realized that
wasn't going to happen.

841
00:47:42.532 --> 00:47:45.234
I refused to ask
out of spite.

842
00:47:45.268 --> 00:47:47.436
I didn't want to give you
the satisfaction

843
00:47:47.471 --> 00:47:50.740
of thinking I cared
enough to ask.

844
00:47:50.775 --> 00:47:54.144
And eventually it became clear that
my spite didn't mean anything to you.

845
00:47:54.179 --> 00:47:57.081
As far as I could tell.
you actually enjoyed it.

846
00:47:57.116 --> 00:47:59.317
So why now?

847
00:48:00.853 --> 00:48:04.822
What harm could Lyanna Stark's
ghost do to either of us

848
00:48:04.856 --> 00:48:08.026
that we haven't done to each other
a hundred times over?

849
00:48:11.964 --> 00:48:14.599
You want to know
the horrible truth?

850
00:48:17.203 --> 00:48:19.838
I can't even remember
what she looked like.

851
00:48:22.675 --> 00:48:27.581
<i>I only know she was the one</i>
<i>thing I ever wanted...</i>

852
00:48:29.217 --> 00:48:33.187
Someone took her
away from me.

853
00:48:33.222 --> 00:48:38.026
and Seven Kingdoms couldn't
fill the hole she left behind.

854
00:48:41.764 --> 00:48:44.466
I felt something
for you once. you know?

855
00:48:45.501 --> 00:48:47.368
I know.

856
00:48:47.403 --> 00:48:50.604
Even after we lost
our first boy.

857
00:48:52.206 --> 00:48:54.307
For quite a while. actually.

858
00:48:58.145 --> 00:49:00.180
<i>Was it ever</i>
<i>possible for us?</i>

859
00:49:00.214 --> 00:49:03.050
Was there ever a time.
ever a moment?

860
00:49:09.791 --> 00:49:11.459
No.

861
00:49:15.465 --> 00:49:18.467
<i>Does that make you feel</i>
<i>better or worse?</i>

862
00:49:22.872 --> 00:49:25.573
It doesn't make me
feel anything.

863
00:49:35.683 --> 00:49:38.985
<i>( Door opens. closes )</i>

864
00:49:40.120 --> 00:49:43.423
She looks like him.
don't she. My Lord?

865
00:49:43.457 --> 00:49:47.361
She has his nose.
his black hair.

866
00:49:47.395 --> 00:49:49.363
Aye.

867
00:49:49.397 --> 00:49:51.532
Tell him when you
see him. My Lord.

868
00:49:51.566 --> 00:49:55.583
If it please you.
tell him how beautiful she is.

869
00:49:56.573 --> 00:49:58.218
I will.

870
00:49:58.243 --> 00:50:00.801
And tell him I've been
with no one else.

871
00:50:01.411 --> 00:50:04.713
I swear it. My Lord.
by the old gods and new.

872
00:50:04.747 --> 00:50:07.048
I don't want no jewels
or nothing.

873
00:50:07.083 --> 00:50:08.983
just him.

874
00:50:09.018 --> 00:50:10.919
The King was always
good to me.

875
00:50:10.953 --> 00:50:13.121
When Jon Arryn
came to visit you.

876
00:50:13.155 --> 00:50:15.022
what did he want?

877
00:50:15.057 --> 00:50:17.157
He wasn't that sort
of man. My Lord.

878
00:50:17.192 --> 00:50:20.360
He just wanted to know
if the child was happy.

879
00:50:20.394 --> 00:50:22.562
healthy.

880
00:50:25.099 --> 00:50:27.300
He looks healthy
enough to me.

881
00:50:29.103 --> 00:50:31.404
The girl shall want
for nothing.

882
00:50:37.345 --> 00:50:39.847
Brothels make a much better
investment than ships.

883
00:50:39.881 --> 00:50:41.416
I've found.

884
00:50:41.450 --> 00:50:44.019
Whores rarely sink.

885
00:50:48.225 --> 00:50:51.194
What do you know
of King Robert's bastards?

886
00:50:51.228 --> 00:50:54.531
Well. he has more
than you. for a start.

887
00:50:54.565 --> 00:50:57.134
- Ned: <i>How many?</i>
- <i>Does it matter?</i>

888
00:50:57.168 --> 00:51:00.237
<i>If you fuck enough women.</i>
<i>some of them will give you presents.</i>

889
00:51:00.271 --> 00:51:02.406
And Jon Arryn tracked
them all down. Why?

890
00:51:02.440 --> 00:51:05.443
He was the King's Hand. Perhaps
Robert wanted them looked after.

891
00:51:05.477 --> 00:51:08.746
He was overcome
with fatherly love.

892
00:51:11.617 --> 00:51:13.284
Come.

893
00:51:19.357 --> 00:51:21.525
- Jory!
- My Lord.

894
00:51:40.346 --> 00:51:42.713
Such a small pack
of wolves.

895
00:51:44.583 --> 00:51:46.351
Stay back. Ser.
This is the Hand of the King.

896
00:51:46.385 --> 00:51:48.419
<i>Was</i> the Hand
of the King.

897
00:51:48.454 --> 00:51:50.088
Now I'm not sure
what he is--

898
00:51:50.122 --> 00:51:52.524
lord of somewhere
very far away.

899
00:51:52.558 --> 00:51:54.993
( Running ) What's the meaning
of this. Lannister?

900
00:51:55.027 --> 00:51:57.395
Get back inside
where it's safe.

901
00:51:57.430 --> 00:51:59.130
I'm looking
for my brother.

902
00:51:59.165 --> 00:52:01.199
You remember my brother.
don't you. Lord Stark?

903
00:52:01.233 --> 00:52:04.902
Blond hair.
sharp tongue. short man.

904
00:52:06.071 --> 00:52:07.605
I remember him well.

905
00:52:07.639 --> 00:52:09.640
It seems he had
some trouble on the road.

906
00:52:09.675 --> 00:52:12.009
You wouldn't know what
happened to him. would you?

907
00:52:12.043 --> 00:52:14.311
He was taken at my command

908
00:52:14.345 --> 00:52:16.546
<i>to answer for his crimes.</i>

909
00:52:17.815 --> 00:52:19.682
- Littlefinger: My lords!
- ( Horse neighs )

910
00:52:19.716 --> 00:52:21.317
I'll bring the City Watch.

911
00:52:23.920 --> 00:52:25.721
Come. Stark.

912
00:52:25.756 --> 00:52:27.156
I'd rather you die
sword in hand.

913
00:52:27.190 --> 00:52:29.825
- If you threaten My Lord again--
- Threaten?

914
00:52:29.860 --> 00:52:32.828
As in. "I'm going
to open your lord

915
00:52:32.862 --> 00:52:36.432
from balls to brains and
see what Starks are made of"?

916
00:52:36.466 --> 00:52:38.800
You kill me.

917
00:52:38.835 --> 00:52:41.436
your brother's
a dead man.

918
00:52:41.471 --> 00:52:43.438
You're right.

919
00:52:43.472 --> 00:52:45.907
Take him alive.
Kill his men.

920
00:52:48.678 --> 00:52:49.812
( Screams )

921
00:53:54.544 --> 00:53:56.111
Yah!

922
00:54:21.072 --> 00:54:23.173
My brother. Lord Stark--

923
00:54:23.208 --> 00:54:25.609
we want him back.

924
00:54:32.384 --> 00:54:35.485
( Neighs )

925
00:54:38.822 --> 00:54:40.823
<i>( Theme music playing )</i>

926
00:54:40.848 --> 00:54:44.848
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==
